u.s. wine export rose 15 per cent last year export of american wine rose 14.9 per cent last year to a total of 7.2 million gallon , the wine institut said . the san francisco-bas promot group said 95 per cent of the export wine wa from california and the top three market were canada , japan and britain . japan , which edg out britain as the lead import of american wine in 1985 , continu in second place . canadian import rose 3.2 per cent to 2.6 million gallon ; japan , 9.9 per cent to 1.2 million gallon , and britain , 20.2 per cent to 962,360 gallon . a spokesman for the institut said the declin valu of the dollar and strong promot effort on the part of the california wine industri contribut significantli to the increas shipment . the 1986 wine export were valu at 34.7 mln dlr , up from 27.6 mln dlr the previou year .